### Bug: Redundant Bloc Access Causes Runtime Errors

<!-- **Medium Severity** -->

<!-- DESCRIPTION START -->
Several `_handle...` methods and `_getCurrentEmailIndex` are trying to ac=
cess the `MailboxBloc` via `context.read<MailboxBloc>()`. Since `_mailbox=
Bloc` is already an instance field of the state, using `context.read` is =
redundant and could lead to runtime errors if the `BuildContext` isn't pr=
operly scoped or the widget is unmounted.
<!-- DESCRIPTION END -->

