<h3 dir=3D"auto">Bug: Redundant Bloc Access Causes Runtime Errors</h3>


<p dir=3D"auto">Several <code class=3D"notranslate">_handle...</code> met=
hods and <code class=3D"notranslate">_getCurrentEmailIndex</code> are try=
ing to access the <code class=3D"notranslate">MailboxBloc</code> via <cod=
e class=3D"notranslate">context.read&lt;MailboxBloc&gt;()</code>. Since <=
code class=3D"notranslate">_mailboxBloc</code> is already an instance fie=
ld of the state, using <code class=3D"notranslate">context.read</code> is=
 redundant and could lead to runtime errors if the <code class=3D"notrans=
late">BuildContext</code> isn't properly scoped or the widget is unmounte=
d.</p>


